#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 8. Verocanaasurindasutta → virocanaasurindasuttaṃ (s1-3, pts2) | virocana-asurindo (attho) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Verocanaasurindasutta "
msgstr "8. Verocana, Lord of Demons "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.486, sc1
msgctxt "sn11.8:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ jetavane. "
msgstr "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.8:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā divāvihāragato hoti paṭisallīno. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha had gone into retreat for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.8:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho sakko ca devānamindo verocano ca asurindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā paccekaṃ dvārabāhaṃ nissāya aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, and Verocana, lord of demons, approached the Buddha and stationed themselves one by each door-post. "

msgctxt "sn11.8:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho verocano asurindo bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Verocana recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

# NOTE: Here I’m keeping the masculine forms. they seem to suit Verocana!
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn11.8:2.1"
msgid "“Vāyametheva puriso, "
msgstr "“A man should make an effort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:2.2"
msgid "yāva atthassa nipphadā; "
msgstr "until his goal is accomplished. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Nipphannasobhano → nipphannasobhino (bj, pts2) | nippannasobhaṇo (pts1) | nipphannasobhaṇo (mr)
#. VAR: attho → atthā (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn11.8:2.3"
msgid "Nipphannasobhano attho, "
msgstr "When goals are accomplished they shine: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:2.4"
msgid "verocanavaco idan”ti. "
msgstr "this is the word of Verocana!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.226, sc3
msgctxt "sn11.8:3.1"
msgid "“Vāyametheva puriso, "
msgstr "“A man should make an effort "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:3.2"
msgid "yāva atthassa nipphadā; "
msgstr "until his goal is accomplished. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Nipphannasobhano attho → nipphannasobhino atthā (bj, s1, km, pts2) | nippannasobhaṇo attho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.8:3.3"
msgid "Nipphannasobhano attho, "
msgstr "Of goals that shine when accomplished, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:3.4"
msgid "khantyā bhiyyo na vijjatī”ti. "
msgstr "none better than patience is found.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.8:4.1"
msgid "“Sabbe sattā atthajātā, "
msgstr "“All beings are goal-orientated, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:4.2"
msgid "tattha tattha yathārahaṃ; "
msgstr "as befits them in each case. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:4.3"
msgid "Saṃyogaparamā tveva, "
msgstr "But connection is the ultimate "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:4.4"
msgid "sambhogā sabbapāṇinaṃ; "
msgstr "of pleasures for all living creatures. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:4.5"
msgid "Nipphannasobhano attho, "
msgstr "When goals are accomplished they shine: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.8:4.6"
msgid "verocanavaco idan”ti. "
msgstr "this is the word of Verocana!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.487, sc5
msgctxt "sn11.8:5.1"
msgid "“Sabbe sattā atthajātā, "
msgstr "“All beings are goal-orientated, "

#. HTML: <br>
